snippet.description:
Should you buy stocks or real estate?

I've invested in stocks and real estate long enough to know which one I prefer to put my time and money into. In this video I break down the 5 main reasons why I prefer to invest in stocks instead of real estate. Stock market investing is far more time efficient than managing rental properties, and real estate investing didn't get any easier or better in 2020 either. Buying stocks is the way to go if you are looking for true passive income.

snippet.title: Stock Market and Election Update 11/5/2020 #shorts #stocks #election
snippet.description:
The stock market was up big yesterday and is looking good again for stocks this morning in premarket hours. Biden is likely to win the presidential election, but the market is up because the senate is going to remain republican, which blocks Biden’s tax plan from going through. With a favorable tax plan currently in place for the market, we are picking up gains now post election after pricing in the Biden win and tax plan pre election. It's 11/5/2020 and we've been watching this election and stock market closely for 2 days now. Will we have a result today?!

By the way, let me know if you like these "shorts" style quick updates in the comments below.

snippet.title: How to Invest in the Stock Market | How to Invest in Stocks
snippet.description:
How to Invest in the Stock Market | How to Invest in Stocks

If you want to learn how to invest in stocks and make money by investing in stocks, this video is for you. In this video I break down how to get started investing in stocks and the stock market. Before opening a taxable investment account, I recommend maxing out a 401K (if your employer offers it) and/or Roth IRA first. Once you are to the point where you are maxed out on annual contributions to those accounts, then starting a taxable investment account makes more financial sense. Choose a brokerage, fund the account, then choose which investment you want to put your money into. I break down brokerages and the different kinds of stock investments to choose from if you are looking for performance similar to the stock market.

snippet.title: S&P 500 vs Dow Jones Industrial Average | Which Stock Market Index is Best?
snippet.description:
S&P 500 vs Dow Jones Industrial Average | Which Stock Market Index is Best?

The Dow Jones Industrial Average Stock Market Index is probably the most commonly referred to stock market index of all time. Yet, the S&P 500 stock market index covers far more companies than the Dow Jones. Why is the Dow Jones still relevant? In this video I compare the two stock market indices and come to a surprising conclusion.

In this video I compare the two stock market indices and come to a surprising conclusion.

snippet.title: Watch This If You Have Debt | How to Get Out of Debt | Dave Ramsey Baby Steps Explained
snippet.description:
In this video I discuss Dave Ramsey and his Baby Steps program designed to show people how to get out of debt and reach financial peace. Dave Ramsey is well known through his radio and TV shows, books, and speaking events. His baby steps include saving for an emergency fund, the debt snowball method, investing for retirement, and eventually becoming free of any major requirements on your money so you are able to do what you want, not what you have to. I explain Dave Ramsey's baby steps program, and also provide my opinion on some of the steps that can be approached in different ways that I feel may be better in some situations, but ultimately reach the same end goal of getting out of debt fast and reaching financial peace.

snippet.title: HOW TO INVEST IN SPORTS TEAMS | Stocks that will get you invested in your team | NFL Sunday Special!
snippet.description:
HOW TO INVEST IN SPORTS TEAMS | Stocks that will get you invested in your team | NFL Sunday Special!

In this video I talk about how we can invest in sports teams, both directly and indirectly. There aren't many teams that are publicly traded, but some of the companies that own those teams are. I talk about NFL football, NBA basketball, NHL hockey, MLB baseball, soccer, and some television networks. Tickers RCI (Rogers Communications, the Toronto teams), MSGS (Madison Square Garden, the New York teams), MANU (Manchester United), BATRK (Liberty Braves Group, the Atlanta Braves), and DIS (Disney, who owns ESPN). 

Let me know what you think and if you enjoyed this content, please like, comment, and subscribe!

Thanks, 

Brad / Money Dad
